President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring October 21-27, 2018 as National Character Counts Week in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of character and integrity in the American citizenry and the role of individuals and leaders in shaping the nation's success. It highlights the responsibility of parents, guardians, teachers, and mentors in teaching valuable traits to young people, such as perseverance, courage, respect, and hard work. The proclamation also mentions the First Lady Melania Trump's BE BEST initiative, which focuses on the emotional, social, and physical well-being of children. It calls for the promotion of acts of service and leadership, and expresses gratitude to those who contribute to raising children of strong character and integrity. The proclamation encourages public officials, educators, parents, students, and all Americans to observe the week with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs.